@section Block operations

@cindex blocks
@cindex selection
@cindex clipboard

Text can be selected (``marked'') for block operations.  There are two
ways to mark text:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{Keyboard}: @kbd{Shift} + any cursor key extends the selection.
Or use @kbd{Ctrl-K B} to set the start and @kbd{Ctrl-K K} to set the end.

@item
@strong{Mouse}: click and drag to select.  In X11,
@kbd{Shift}-click extends the selection.
@end enumerate

@multitable @columnfractions .35 .25 .25
@headitem Action @tab Menu @tab Chord
@item Begin mark @tab @kbd{Alt-B B} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K B}
@item End mark @tab @kbd{Alt-B E} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K K}
@item Mark line @tab @kbd{Alt-B L} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K L}
@item Mark all @tab @kbd{Alt-B W} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K X}
@item Go to block start @tab @kbd{Alt-B G} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K A}
@item Go to block end @tab @kbd{Alt-B N} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K Z}
@item Copy block @tab @kbd{Alt-B C} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K C}
@item Move block @tab @kbd{Alt-B M} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K V}
@item Delete block @tab @kbd{Alt-B D} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K Y}
@item Hide marks @tab @kbd{Alt-B H} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K H}
@item Read file into block @tab @kbd{Alt-B R} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K R}
@item Write block to file @tab @kbd{Alt-B W} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K W}
@item Indent block @tab @kbd{Alt-B I} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K I}
@item Unindent block @tab @kbd{Alt-B T} @tab @kbd{Ctrl-K U}
@end multitable

Cut, copy, and paste use the Edit menu:

@table @kbd
@item Alt-E T
Cut (delete marked text and copy to clipboard).
@item Alt-E C
Copy (copy marked text to clipboard).
@item Alt-E P
Paste (insert clipboard at cursor).
@item Alt-E S
Show clipboard contents.
@end table

@section Search and replace

@cindex search
@cindex replace
@cindex regular expressions
@cindex regex

Open the search dialog with @kbd{Alt-S F} (Find) or @kbd{Alt-S R}
(Replace).  Both dialogs share the same options, accessible via
@kbd{Alt-@var{letter}}:

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .25 .60
@headitem Key @tab Option @tab Description
@item @kbd{Alt-T} @tab Text @tab The string to search for.
@item @kbd{Alt-N} @tab New String @tab Replacement text (Replace only).
@item @kbd{Alt-C} @tab Case Sensitive @tab Distinguish upper/lower case.
@item @kbd{Alt-W} @tab Whole Words @tab Match complete words only.
@item @kbd{Alt-R} @tab Regular Expressions @tab Enable regex mode.
@item @kbd{Alt-P} @tab Prompt @tab Ask before each replacement.
@item @kbd{Alt-D} @tab Forward @tab Search forward from cursor.
@item @kbd{Alt-B} @tab Backward @tab Search backward from cursor.
@item @kbd{Alt-G} @tab Global @tab Search the entire file.
@item @kbd{Alt-S} @tab Block @tab Search only within the marked block.
@item @kbd{Alt-F} @tab From Cursor @tab Start from current position.
@item @kbd{Alt-E} @tab From Start @tab Start from beginning of file/block.
@item @kbd{Alt-A} @tab Replace All @tab Replace all matches (Replace only).
@end multitable

Press @key{Return} to find/replace the next match, @key{ESC} to cancel.

@subsection Regular expression syntax

@cindex egrep

xwpe uses @command{egrep}-compatible regular expressions:

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .85
@headitem Pattern @tab Meaning
@item @code{^} @tab Beginning of line.
@item @code{$} @tab End of line.
@item @code{.} @tab Any single character.
@item @code{[abc]} @tab Any character in the set.
@item @code{[^abc]} @tab Any character NOT in the set.
@item @code{[a-z]} @tab Any character in the range.
@item @code{*} @tab Previous character repeated zero or more times.
@item @code{+} @tab Previous character repeated one or more times.
@item @code{?} @tab Previous character zero or one time.
@item @code{\|} @tab Alternation (OR).
@item @code{\} @tab Escape the next character.
@end multitable

@section Markers

@cindex markers
@cindex bookmarks

xwpe supports 9 position markers (numbered 1--9).  Set a marker with
@kbd{Ctrl-K @var{n}} where @var{n} is 1--9.  Jump to a marker with
@kbd{Ctrl-O @var{n}}.  (Documented since v1.4.)

@section File manager

@cindex file manager

The file manager (@kbd{Alt-F M}) provides a full-screen file browser
for opening, copying, moving, renaming, and deleting files.

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .25 .60
@headitem Key @tab Field @tab Action
@item @kbd{Alt-N} @tab Name @tab Enter a file name or mask (e.g.@: @code{*.c}).
@item @kbd{Alt-F} @tab Files @tab Select a file from the list.
@item @kbd{Alt-D} @tab Directory @tab Enter a directory path.
@item @kbd{Alt-T} @tab Tree @tab Display the directory tree.
@item @kbd{Alt-C} @tab Change @tab Change to the entered directory.
@item @kbd{Alt-E} @tab Edit @tab Open the selected file for editing.
@item @kbd{Alt-M} @tab Move @tab Rename or move a file.
@item @kbd{Alt-R} @tab Remove @tab Delete a file (to wastebasket or disk).
@item @kbd{Alt-L} @tab Link @tab Create a hard or symbolic link.
@item @kbd{Alt-O} @tab Copy @tab Copy a file.
@item @kbd{Alt-K} @tab Make Dir @tab Create a new directory.
@item @kbd{Alt-A} @tab Attributes @tab Change file permissions.
@item @kbd{Alt-S} @tab Save @tab Save with the name in the Name field.
@item @key{ESC} @tab @tab Close the file manager.
@end multitable

Additional file manager keys (documented since v1.4):

@table @kbd
@item Alt-P
Replace the current editor window with the file in the Name field.
@item Alt-U
Duplicate the marked file.  The new name is @file{@var{name}.dup}.
@end table

File masks use shell glob syntax: @code{*} matches any characters,
@code{[a-z]} matches a single character in the range.

The Name field accepts three kinds of input:

@enumerate
@item
An existing file name: pressing @key{Return} opens it for editing.
@item
A non-existing file name: pressing @key{Return} creates a new file.
@item
A file mask (e.g.@: @code{*.c}, @code{[a-z]*}): pressing @key{Return}
filters the file list.
@end enumerate

(Documented since v1.4.)

@section Automatic indentation

@cindex auto-indent
@cindex indentation

The auto-indent mode can be selected in @samp{Options @result{} Editor}
(@kbd{Alt-O E}).  Three modes are available: auto-indent for compiled
files only, auto-indent for all files, or no auto-indent.
(Documented since v1.4.)

When auto-indent is enabled, the following keys have special behaviour:

@table @key
@item Return
The new line is indented to the beginning column of the previous line.

@item Tab
If @key{Tab} is entered before the first visible character on the line,
the entire line is indented to match the previous line.  If the cursor
is past that column, the line is indented N characters beyond the
previous line (where N is the Tab Stops setting).  If the cursor is
between visible characters, a literal tab is inserted.

@item Backspace
If entered before the first visible character on a line, the line is
re-indented to match the most recent previous line that started at a
lesser column.
@end table
